        {"d":"ltr","words":[{"w":"This is a revision lesson. It contains only two new words:"}]},
        {"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"فِيهِ / فِيهَا","sp":[0,3,3,5,8,11,11]},{"w":"and"},{"w":"أُحِبُّ"}]},
        {"d":"ltr","words":[{"w":"1. فِي means \"in it\", e.g. "}]},
        {"d":"ltr","mode":"text", "words":[{"w":"Who is in the house?"}]},
        {"mode":"text", "words":[{"w":"مَنْ"},{"w":"فِي"},{"w":"البَيتِ؟","sp":[0,2]}]},
        {"d":"ltr","mode":"text", "words":[{"w":"There are my father and mother in it."}]},
        {"mode":"text", "words":[{"w":"فِيهِ","sp":[0,3,3,5],"e":"in it"},{"w":"أَبِي","sp":[4],"e":"father"},{"w":"وَأُمِّي.","e":"mother","sp":[0,2,7,8]}]},
        {"d":"ltr","words":[{"w":"2. The femine is فِيهَا e.g. "}]},
        {"d":"ltr","mode":"text", "words":[{"w":"Who is in the room?"}]},
        {"mode":"text", "words":[{"w":"مَنْ"},{"w":"فِي"},{"w":"الغُرْفَةِ؟","e":"room","sp":[0,2]}]},
        {"d":"ltr","mode":"text", "words":[{"w":"There is my brother in it."}]},
        {"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"فِيهَا","e":"in it","sp":[0,3,3]},{"w":"أَخِي.","e":"brother","sp":[4,5]}] },
        {"d":"ltr","words":[{"w":"3. أُحِبُّ means \"I love, I like\" e.g. "}]},
        {"d":"ltr","mode":"text", "words":[{"w":"I love my father, my mother, my brother and my sister."}]},
        {"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"أُحِبُّ"},{"w":"أَبِي","sp":[4]},{"w":"وَأُمِّي","sp":[0,2,7]},{"w":"وَأَخِي","sp":[0,2,6]},{"w":"وَأُخْتِي","sp":[0,2,8]}] },
        {"d":"ltr","words":[{"w":"The object of verb is in accusative case (مَنْصُوبٌ) i.e. takes <<-a>> ending. But it does not appear in a noun which has the possessive pronoun of the first person singular attached to it. Here are some examples of the object without the possessive pronoun of the first person:"}]},
        {"d":"ltr","mode":"text","words":[{"w":"I love Allah."}]},
        {"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"أُحِبُّ"},{"w":"اللَّهَ."}]},
        {"d":"ltr","mode":"text","words":[{"w":"I love the Messenger."}]},
        {"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"أُحِبُّ"},{"w":"الرَّسُولَ."}]},
        {"d":"ltr","mode":"text","words":[{"w":"I love the Messenger of Allah."}]},
        {"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"أُحِبُّ"},{"w":"رَسُولَ"},{"w":"اللَّهِ."}]},
        {"d":"ltr","mode":"text","words":[{"w":"I love Arabic language."}]},
        {"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"أُحِبُّ"},{"w":"اللُّغَةَ","sp":[0,2]},{"w":"الهَرَبِيَّةَ.","sp":[0,2]}]},
        {"d":"ltr","words":[{"w":"Here we can learn تُحِبُّ \"you love\" (masculine singular)."}]},
        {"d":"ltr","mode":"text","words":[{"w":"Do you love Allah?"}]},
        {"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"أَتُحِبُّ","sp":[0,2]},{"w":"اللَّهَ؟"}]},
        {"d":"ltr","mode":"text","words":[{"w":"Do you love your language?"}]},
        {"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"أَتُحِبُّ","sp":[0,2]},{"w":"لُغَتَكَ؟","sp":[6,8]}]},
        {"d":"ltr","mode":"text","words":[{"w":"Whom do you love?"}]},
        {"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"مَنْ"},{"w":"تُحِبُّ؟"}]},
        {"d":"ltr","mode":"text","words":[{"w":"What do you like?"}]},
        {"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"مَاذَا"},{"w":"تُحِبُّ؟"}]},
        {"d":"ltr","words":[{"w":"Note: In english the word \"and\" is used only before the last word, but in Arabic it must be used all through. "}]}

